<L>__{interior whale house dudley night (1908)}
<A>__{a rough pencil outline of the same painting. whale, age 16, sits on his bed, ignoring the roughhousing of the three younger brothers who share the room. the door opens and whale's mother sarah enters.}
<C>__{sarah whale}
<D>__{jimmy. the privy needs cleaning.}
<C>__{whale}
<D>__{i have my class tonight.}
<A>__{both have midlands accents, like head colds that flatten their speech. whale holds up the sketch to show his mother.}
<C>__{sarah whale}
<D>__{don't get above yarself, jimmy. leave the drawring to the artists.}
<A>__{whale squeezes the pad behind the bed, jumps up.}
<C>__{whale}
<D>__{quite so, mum. to the privy.}
<A>__{and he heads cheerfully out of the room. his mother shakes her head.}
